Package edu.ncsu.csc216.ticket_manager.model.ticket

Class Ticket

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.ticket_manager.model.ticket.Ticket
  • public class Ticket
extends java.lang.Object
    This concrete Class represents the state of the Ticket and allows for keeping track of state and all ticket information. Also, encapsulates all 6 state classes for a Ticket.
    Author:
    John Widdifield

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  Ticket.CanceledState
      This is the state that a ticket is in after it is canceled.
      static class  Ticket.Category
      Category Enumeration for all possible Categories for a Ticket
      class  Ticket.ClosedState
      This is the state that a ticket is in once the IT staff and the client have agreed that the Ticket is Complete (for now).
      class  Ticket.FeedbackState
      This is the state that a ticket is in while it is awaiting feedback from someone
      class  Ticket.NewState
      This is the state that a new ticket is in before any interaction.
      static class  Ticket.Priority
      Priority Enumeration for all possible Priorities of a Ticket
      class  Ticket.ResolvedState
      This is the state that a ticket is in once someone is finished working on it and it has been resolved.
      static class  Ticket.TicketType
      TicketType Enumeration for all possible Types of a Ticket
      class  Ticket.WorkingState
      This is the state that a ticket is in once someone is working on it.
